metadata.name: Millefoglie #282
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

metadata.name: Brownian Stitch #21
metadata.description:
What happens when my grandma's embroidery magazines get a Fractional Brownian motion.

This 3D artwork made with cables.gl has basic orbit controls and the embroidery texture has a 24% chance of being symmetric.

- Press 'P' to play/stop animation.
- Press 'S' to save a screenshot (live-view mode only).

metadata.name: Phantom Voids: An algorithm study #52
metadata.description:
This is the first series of my algorithmic studies. This study is an exploration of algorithms  to create an abstract artwork using only lines. Multiple color palettes with high color contrast have been used. It takes a short time to complete.

Open it in the live mode, it will be saved automatically after completion.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Provence #395
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.name: NO ROADMAP #208
metadata.description:
This collection represents the need we have to move forward despite the obstacles that the road may present us.
We identify ourselves with the one who, even without the most optimal conditions, continues on its way until the goal is reached
Web 3.0 is a space that appears to us without a roadmap, so that everyone can explore it and learn.
Even though we only get to have a skateboard, in this journey of work and effort, we will continue asking ourselves until we can at last get it
WEN LAMBO?

+ 100 Roaders + Color variations
+ 50 Backgrounds + Color variations
+ 30 Foreground
+ 50 Animals
+ 25 Foreground elements
+ 10 Police cars on fire

metadata.description: Each item is a line rotated around a point by an angle. With each step, we adjust both the angle of rotation, and which point on the line we're rotating around. In some cases, we may also allow the rotational point/item to drift by some random amount.

metadata.name: - Still-Life with Flowers - #2
metadata.description:
- Still-Life with Flowers - a generative take on a classic artistic motif.  

The term ‘still-life’ derives from the Dutch word ‘stilleven’, roughly translated it means ‘arrangement of inanimate objects’. Over the centuries, artists have used the ‘still-life genre to try out new techniques and experiment with composition and arrangements. 

- Still-Life with Flowers - is my attempt to (humbly) follow in the footsteps of the artists that contributed to the still life genre and made it into the iconic artistic style it is today.


- Still-Life with Flowers - consists of 256 Flower arrangements (mintable iterations) celebrating compositional experiments and the artistic arrangement of inanimate objects !

For every iteration, over 200 random number generators (fxrand) are triggered to create a unique floral arrangement. (no images were used to create this Artwork)

—

Press R to toggle the animation on / off

Press X to reset 

—

I want to thank everyone who helped me realize this project.
(you know who you are ; )
This project took a long time to make, it was a pretty bumpy road and I could not have done it without your generosity and patience ! 

Made with cables.gl (check it out, it is amazing !)
